{
  "texts": [
    "Users are encouraged to share their experiences with the benchmark, such as posting results, writing tutorials, or comparing models, in forums or social media, as long as they credit the source.",
    "We have set up a discussion board (or use an existing platform like the Hugging Face forums or a Discord channel) for the benchmark where people can ask questions, suggest improvements, or seek help.",
    "The expectation is that community members will help each other, making the benchmarking process easier and more standardized.",
    "For example, if someone has trouble using a particular dataset, others who have used it can chime in with advice.",
    "This kind of peer support is invaluable."
  ]
}